OL,4,G0600FSherlock Holmes
OL,5,     GA young boy and his father are
OL,6,     Gtraveling on a train, and after
OL,7,     Gthey have a fight, the boy runs
OL,8,     Gout of the compartment and seems
OL,9,     Gto have vanished into thin air.
OL,10,G0630FSherlock Holmes
OL,11,     GAlex, an advice columnist,
OL,12,     Gadvises a young woman, to break
OL,13,     Gup with her violent fiance. The
OL,14,     Ggroom-to-be pretends to be
OL,15,     Gwealthy to mask his motive of
OL,16,     Gacquiring the wealth of his
OL,17,     Gintended bride.
OL,18,G0700FSherlock Holmes
OL,19,     GA baby is left on Holmes' and
OL,20,     GWatson's doorstep. The child
OL,21,     Gturns out to be the daughter of a
OL,22,     Gmissing French scientist.
